==Korean==
===Noun===
'''학''' (''hag, hak'')
# ([[鶴]]) [[crane]], cf. the prefix of [[hagiography]] 

====Synonyms====
* [[두루미]] (''durumi'') [[crane]], cf. Hungarian [[daru]] (perhaps of Sumerian origin), Japanese [[鶴]] (つる, tsuru)  

====Derived terms====
* [[백학]] ([[白鶴]], ''baeghag, baekhak'') [[crane]], literally,"white crane"
* [[선학]] ([[仙鶴]], ''seon-hag, -hak'') [[crane]] (as a sacred bird), literally, "hagio-crane"
* [[학가]] ([[鶴駕]], ''-ga'') [[crown prince]]'s going out of the palace 
* [[학반]] ([[鶴班]], ''-ban'') nobility of [[civil]] [[class]] 
* [[학발]] ([[鶴髮]], ''-bal'') [[silvery]] [[hair]] like a white crane  
* [[학수]] ([[鶴壽]], ''-su'') wishing someone a [[long]] [[life]]  
* 학[[춤]] (''-chum'') [[dance]] in the disguise of a crane
* [[홍학]] ([[紅鶴]], ''honghag'') [[flamingo]], literally, "red crane"

====See also====
* [[해오라기]] (''haeoragi'') white [[heron]], [[egret]]
* [[황새]] (''hwangsae'') [[stork]]

